hey can apply to college. Additionally, several mechanisms reinforce the reproduction of social inequality, showing how institutions and families of the middle and upper-middle class work to procure advantages by cultivating dispositions among their children for specific types of higher education opportunities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChildren with social disabilitiesxEducation. 0aCollege choice. 0aEducational equalization. 0aUniversities and collegesxAdmissionxSocial aspects. 7aEDUCATION / General.2bisacsh  aclass, inequality, education, academia, college, college admissions, working-class, middle-class, Bay Area, San Francisco, university.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2023 Englishz978311131910008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Communication 2023z9783111318141oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079130340uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197882708040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978827080423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978827080/original  a978-3-11-079130-3  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131910-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-SEWb2023